Licensee agrees to indemnify, defend, and hold Inexas harmless for any 
liability incurred by, or claims asserted against the Licensee by reason of 
accepting any such warranty or additional liability.

 

3. Royalties
a) Table of fees

Royalties are defined in the Table of Fees for the specific Software Package 
under License

b) Exceptions

The Legal Entity is exempt from Royalties if one or more of the following 
conditions are met:

The Software Package is not employed for Day-to-Day use.
The Legal Entity has less that thirty full-time equivalent employees.
The Legal Entity is a officially recognised non-governmental not-for-profit 
organization.
c) Penalties

If a legal entity fails to pay Royalties due within 90 days of start of 
Day-to-Day Use then the Legal Entity will incur a one-time penalty charge 
equal to 10 times the initial Royalty fees and not less that USD 100 in 
addition to the standard Royalties. It is the sole responsibility of the 
Licensee to ensure that Royalties are paid when due, Inexas will not send 
reminders.

d) Refunds

No refunds will be given. This clause applies in situations not limited to 
the following cases: Software and/or derived works no longer used; the Legal 
Entity changes status to become not-for-profit or less than 30 Full Time 
Employees.

4. Poison pill clause

Inexas retains ownership of the software. In the event of the Inexas changing 
ownership for the minimum legal amount (effectively free of charge) to 
another organization other than a contributor owned cooperative, ownership of 
the accompanying Software Package immediately reverts to the public domain.

